    content: [
      {
        heading: "Check the integration status first",
        body: "Go to **Settings → Integrations**. Each connected source shows a status indicator:\n\n- **Green (Active):** syncing normally\n- **Yellow (Warning):** last sync completed but with some errors — data is partial\n- **Red (Error):** sync has failed — no new data since the last successful sync\n- **Grey (Paused):** sync has been manually paused or your plan has been downgraded\n\nClick the integration name to see the last sync timestamp and any error message.",
      },
      {
        heading: "Re-authorise the connection",
        body: "The most common cause of a sync stopping is an expired or revoked authorisation token. This happens when:\n- You changed your password on the connected platform\n- A team member who authorised the connection left the business and their account was deactivated\n- The connected platform revoked third-party access\n\nTo fix: click **Reconnect** on the failing integration and go through the OAuth flow again. This refreshes the authorisation without losing your historical data.",
      },
      {
        heading: "Check your plan limits",
        body: "Some integrations are only available on certain plans. If you recently downgraded your AskBiz plan, integrations not supported on your new plan will be paused automatically. Check **Settings → Plan** to see which integrations your current plan supports.",
      },
      {
        heading: "Trigger a manual sync",
        body: "If the integration shows Active but data still looks stale, trigger a manual sync: **Settings → Integrations → [Platform] → Sync Now**. Allow up to 10 minutes for the sync to complete. Refresh your dashboard after the sync finishes.",
      },
      {
        heading: "Still not working?",
        body: "If re-authorising and manual sync do not resolve the issue, contact support via the chat icon in the bottom right of your dashboard. Include:\n- Which integration is failing\n- The error message shown in Settings → Integrations\n- When the issue started\n\nOur team typically responds within 2 hours on business days.",
      },
    ],
    faq: [
      { q: "How do I know how long my data has been out of date?", a: "Go to Settings → Integrations and click the integration name. The Last Successful Sync timestamp shows exactly when data was last pulled successfully." },
      { q: "Will I lose historical data if I disconnect and reconnect an integration?", a: "No. Disconnecting an integration pauses future syncs but does not delete the historical data already in AskBiz. When you reconnect, AskBiz resumes syncing from where it left off." },
    ],
