        heading: "Why a 13-week cash flow forecast?",
        body: "The 13-week (quarterly) cash flow forecast is the standard used by CFOs and turnaround specialists because it is short enough to be accurate but long enough to see problems coming. Revenue and P&L forecasts tell you whether you are profitable — the cash flow forecast tells you whether you will run out of money.\n\nA business can be profitable on paper and still run out of cash. This happens when customers pay slowly (long debtor days), when you pay suppliers quickly, or when a large VAT or tax payment falls due. The cash flow forecast makes these timing mismatches visible.",
