        heading: "Why blended CAC misleads",
        body: "Blended CAC (total marketing spend ÷ total new customers) averages across all campaigns and channels. It tells you what you are paying on average but hides enormous variation — a campaign with a £15 CAC and a campaign with a £120 CAC both contribute to a blended figure of maybe £45.\n\nIf you scale based on blended CAC, you may be scaling the expensive campaigns along with the efficient ones. Campaign-level CAC tells you which campaigns to pour budget into and which to pause.\n\nAskBiz calculates CAC at the campaign level for all connected ad platforms.",
