        body: "Social media platforms are designed to show you metrics that make you feel good about your content — likes, follower counts, impressions. These are called vanity metrics because they feel important but rarely correlate with business outcomes.\n\nBusiness metrics for social media are different:\n- **Traffic from social** — how many sessions on your website came from social channels?\n- **Conversion rate from social traffic** — of those sessions, how many converted to purchase?\n- **Revenue attributed to social** — total sales where social was a touchpoint in the attribution path\n- **CAC from social** — cost per new customer acquired via social (paid and organic combined)\n- **Follower-to-buyer conversion rate** — what % of your social followers have ever purchased?",
